HEADWORD: fool around
<hw>fool` a*round"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Fooled around</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Fooling around</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
waste time in idle pursuits; to fool{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fool{2}.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To flirt or philander.</def> <au>RHUD</au>br/
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To be sexually promiscuous; to engage in sexual
intercourse with more than one partner; especially, to engage in
adultery; <as>as, to <ex>fool around</ex> with another
woman</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fool around with</ent>⟦br⟧
